      • endTime

      • mainBody

        Main body id constant.

      • secondaryBody

        Secondary body id constant, if anyone exists.

      • eventType

        public MoonEventElement.EVENT eventType
        Event id code. Constants defined in this class.

      • details

        public java.lang.String details
        Holds details on the event. For mutual events it contains a number with the percentage of eclipse/occultation, the date of that maximum, and the distance between both bodies in degrees.

      • subType

        public MoonEventElement.SUBEVENT subType
        Subevent id constant. Only takes sense on mutual events with the mother planet, while a satellite is partially eclipsed or occulted. In this case the event marks the beggining or the ending of the period when the satellite is fully eclipsed or occulted. Constants defined in this class.

      • visibleFromEarth

        public boolean visibleFromEarth
        True for a visible event, false otherwise. Note a given event must be visible from Earth and with positive elevation to be observable.

      • elevation

        public double elevation
        Elevation of the source in radians above the observer, calculated even if requested ephemerides are geocentric.

      • severalSimultaneousEvents

        public boolean severalSimultaneousEvents
        This flag is false always except when calculating natural satellites events (mutual and non-mutual). In this case this flag will be true for those events that are simultaneous (several events going on at the same time). In practice, this flag is true always for non-mutual events involving two or more satellites, and also true always for mutual events (since they involve two satellites).

      • EVENTS

        public static final java.lang.String[] EVENTS
        Holds a description of the events.
